FREE USE — NO LICENSE REQUIRED
================================

The Plugin may be used at no charge by:

  • Individuals using it on a personal workstation for personal,
    portfolio, or skill-development purposes.
  • Students and educators for coursework, academic research, or
    classroom instruction.
  • Open productions where the final work is released publicly without
    charge and the pipeline tooling is not sold or licensed.
  • Open-source contributors evaluating or extending the Plugin to
    submit patches upstream.
  • Commercial studios during an internal evaluation period not
    exceeding 30 days.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

COMMERCIAL USE — LICENSE REQUIRED
===================================

A commercial license is required when the Plugin is used:

  • As part of any commercial studio pipeline (VFX, animation,
    advertising, games, or motion graphics), regardless of seat count.
  • To automate or accelerate billable client work or paid productions.
  • On a render farm or shared server integrated with commercial render
    managers (Deadline, Tractor, Royal Render, etc.).
  • Inside a proprietary tool, SaaS product, or enterprise platform
    distributed to third parties.
  • In any deployment where Houdini is used for revenue-generating
    production work and the Plugin bridges or automates part of that
    workflow.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

HOW TO OBTAIN A COMMERCIAL LICENSE
=====================================

Contact:  contact@vibrante-node.com
Website:  https://vibrante-node.com

Please include:
  - Studio or organisation name and size
  - Intended deployment scope (seats, pipeline components, geography)
  - Expected start date

See COMMERCIAL_LICENSE.md in the project root for full commercial
terms, tier pricing (Studio Seat / Studio Pipeline / Enterprise), and
restrictions.

